b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. JetBrains AI is best suited for JetBrains IDE users, Java/Kotlin developers, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Replit AI, meanwhile, shines for beginners learning to code, rapid prototyping in browser, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2023, JetBrains AI describes itself as \"AI assistant built into JetBrains IDEs.\" Replit AI, established in 2016, positions itself as \"Build software faster with AI in your browser.\" With 7 years between them, Replit AI brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while JetBrains AI offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **JetBrains AI** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (9 vs 5), more competitive pricing. However, this does not mean Replit AI is a poor choice — far from it. Replit AI excels in its own right, particularly for beginners learning to code and rapid prototyping in browser.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value deep jetbrains ide integration, go with JetBrains AI. If zero setup cloud environment matters more to you, Replit AI is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
